00:24:27,566 --> 00:24:31,434
l'm not one
to meddle, but...

605
00:24:31,503 --> 00:24:34,233
are you all right?

606
00:24:34,306 --> 00:24:36,672
Are you in pain?

607
00:24:36,741 --> 00:24:38,834
No.

608
00:24:38,910 --> 00:24:41,208
But thanks.

609
00:24:41,279 --> 00:24:43,110
Ok, well,
l'm right up here.

610
00:24:43,181 --> 00:24:44,944
l'm just studying
for the bar exam,

611
00:24:45,016 --> 00:24:47,576
so if you need
anything,

612
00:24:47,652 --> 00:24:49,119
just holler at me.

613
00:24:49,187 --> 00:24:50,415
Ok.

614
00:24:50,489 --> 00:24:52,013
Anything. All right?

615
00:24:52,090 --> 00:24:54,388
l'll get it for you.

616
00:24:57,496 --> 00:24:58,929
My name is Rudy Baylor.

617
00:24:58,997 --> 00:25:00,521
Kelly Riker.
Nice to meet you.

618
00:25:00,599 --> 00:25:03,466
Kelly, it's nice
to meet you, too.

619
00:25:03,535 --> 00:25:05,526
Why don't you sit down?

620
00:25:05,604 --> 00:25:08,334
Go ahead. Take a seat.

621
00:25:13,078 --> 00:25:17,037
What school do you go to?

622
00:25:18,517 --> 00:25:20,075
I went
to Austin Peay

623
00:25:20,151 --> 00:25:22,449
and then law school
at Memphis State.

624
00:25:25,524 --> 00:25:27,924
I always wanted
to go to college,

625
00:25:27,993 --> 00:25:32,259
but it didn't work out.

626
00:25:32,330 --> 00:25:33,388
Did you?

627
00:25:33,465 --> 00:25:35,558
Yeah. I always
thought l'd go,

628
00:25:35,634 --> 00:25:37,363
but it didn't work out.

629
00:25:37,435 --> 00:25:40,427
What kind of lawyer
do you want to be?

630
00:25:40,505 --> 00:25:45,442
Well, I enjoy trial
work, so, uh...

631
00:25:45,510 --> 00:25:49,241
l'd like to spend my
days in the courtroom.

632
00:25:49,314 --> 00:25:52,613
Defending criminals?

633
00:25:52,684 --> 00:25:54,174
Maybe.

634
00:25:54,252 --> 00:25:55,617
Maybe.

