00:25:55,687 --> 00:25:58,656
They're entitled
to a good defense.

636
00:25:58,723 --> 00:26:00,987
They have a right
to their day in court.

637
00:26:01,059 --> 00:26:02,856
Murderers?

638
00:26:05,463 --> 00:26:09,524
Most murderers can't
afford a private lawyer.

639
00:26:11,670 --> 00:26:14,230
Rapists and...

640
00:26:14,306 --> 00:26:17,036
child molesters?

641
00:26:18,810 --> 00:26:20,437
No.

642
00:26:20,512 --> 00:26:23,106
Men who beat their wives?

643
00:26:35,293 --> 00:26:38,456
Criminal work is
a real rare specialty.

644
00:26:38,530 --> 00:26:41,727
Um, l'll probably
be doing more, uh...

645
00:26:41,800 --> 00:26:44,325
civil litigation.

646
00:26:44,402 --> 00:26:45,369
[Cell Phone Rings]

647
00:26:45,437 --> 00:26:46,699
Like lawsuits and stuff.

648
00:26:46,771 --> 00:26:47,669
Right.

649
00:26:47,739 --> 00:26:48,706
Yeah.

650
00:26:48,773 --> 00:26:51,742
[Ring]

651
00:26:51,810 --> 00:26:53,368
lt's, uh...
Excuse me.

652
00:26:53,445 --> 00:26:54,605
Mm-hmm.

653
00:26:54,679 --> 00:26:56,840
[Ring]

654
00:26:59,651 --> 00:27:02,142
[Ring]

655
00:27:02,220 --> 00:27:03,312
Rudy Baylor.

656
00:27:03,388 --> 00:27:05,379
Hey. Hey there.
lt's me.

657
00:27:05,457 --> 00:27:06,651
What you doing?

658
00:27:06,725 --> 00:27:08,625
How's the fishing
going?

659
00:27:08,693 --> 00:27:11,161
Um, it's, uh,
it's going well.

660
00:27:11,229 --> 00:27:13,254
l'm actually talking
to the prospect right now.

661
00:27:13,331 --> 00:27:15,629
Bruiser: Well, you
better sign her up.

662
00:27:15,700 --> 00:27:18,669
What--Rudy? Rudy?
Can you hear me?

663
00:27:18,737 --> 00:27:19,965
I enjoyed meeting you.

664
00:27:20,038 --> 00:27:21,266
Rudy?

665
00:27:21,339 --> 00:27:23,500
Yeah, thanks
for the company.

666
00:27:23,575 --> 00:27:25,941
Hey, tomorrow night?

667
00:27:26,011 --> 00:27:28,070
Maybe.

668
00:27:43,194 --> 00:27:44,923
Man: Time's up.
Pencils down.

669
00:27:44,996 --> 00:27:46,964
Please pass your test booklets
to your right

670
00:27:47,032 --> 00:27:48,863
so that your proctors
may gather them up.

671
00:27:48,933 --> 00:27:50,798
Rudy: ln my first year
at law school,

672
00:27:50,869 --> 00:27:52,962
everybody loved
everybody else

673
00:27:53,038 --> 00:27:55,029
because we were all
studying the law,

674
00:27:55,106 --> 00:27:57,574
and the law
was a noble thing.

675
00:27:57,642 --> 00:27:59,439
By my third year,

676
00:27:59,511 --> 00:28:02,241
you were lucky if you weren't
murdered in your sleep.

677
00:28:02,313 --> 00:28:03,439
People stole exams,

678
00:28:03,515 --> 00:28:05,779
hid research materials
from the library,

679
00:28:05,850 --> 00:28:07,477
and lied to the professors.

680
00:28:10,055 --> 00:28:13,286
Such is the nature
of the profession.

681
00:28:18,196 --> 00:28:19,629
Right here.

682
00:28:19,698 --> 00:28:22,132
Rudy: Half an hour ago,
her husband came in...

683
00:28:22,200 --> 00:28:24,100
and threw a bowl
of soup at her

684
00:28:24,169 --> 00:28:26,103
because she just won't
get it through her head

685
00:28:26,171 --> 00:28:27,832
how much he loves her.

686
00:28:27,906 --> 00:28:30,067
This is my room.

687
00:28:30,141 --> 00:28:33,133
Pregnant at 18, married,
then a miscarriage--

688
00:28:33,211 --> 00:28:35,145
probably because
he beat her up--

689
00:28:35,213 --> 00:28:37,238
and still,
she can't leave him.

690
00:28:37,315 --> 00:28:39,579
You are gonna
have to help me.

691
00:28:39,651 --> 00:28:40,913
Rudy:
Everything l've ever seen

692
00:28:40,985 --> 00:28:43,317
tells me that this girl
is a loser,

693
00:28:43,388 --> 00:28:46,221
scarred and broken
and maybe even dangerous,

694
00:28:46,291 --> 00:28:49,089
but l've never really seen
anyone like her before,

695
00:28:49,160 --> 00:28:50,320
and instead of running away,

696
00:28:50,395 --> 00:28:53,853
all I want to do
is protect her.

697
00:29:15,653 --> 00:29:19,419
Visiting hours are over, hon.
You kids need to wrap it up.

698
00:29:25,497 --> 00:29:27,021
[Chuckles]

699
00:29:39,577 --> 00:29:41,602
So...

700
00:29:41,679 --> 00:29:44,341
He should be shot.

701
00:29:44,415 --> 00:29:47,680
Any man who'd beat his wife
with an aluminum bat

702
00:29:47,752 --> 00:29:48,946
needs to be shot.

703
00:29:50,688 --> 00:29:52,622
How did you find out?

704
00:29:52,690 --> 00:29:54,920
There are police reports,
there are ambulance reports,

705
00:29:54,993 --> 00:29:57,427
there are hospital records.

706
00:29:57,495 --> 00:29:58,985
How long are you
gonna wait, Kelly,

707
00:29:59,063 --> 00:30:01,088
until he decides
to hit you in the head

708
00:30:01,166 --> 00:30:02,758
with that bat of his?

709
00:30:02,834 --> 00:30:04,961
'Cause that could kill you,
you know. That'd be it.

710
00:30:05,036 --> 00:30:06,401
A couple of good shots
to the skull,

711
00:30:06,471 --> 00:30:07,460
and that would be it.

712
00:30:07,539 --> 00:30:10,337
Stop it.
Don't tell me how it feels.

713
00:30:16,681 --> 00:30:18,444
Look at me, Kelly.

714
00:30:18,516 --> 00:30:20,347
Can I ask you something?

715
00:30:23,955 --> 00:30:27,152
Do you have a father
or a brother?

716
00:30:28,893 --> 00:30:30,155
Why?

717
00:30:31,262 --> 00:30:32,524
Because if my daughter

718
00:30:32,597 --> 00:30:34,360
got beat the way
your husband beat you,

719
00:30:34,432 --> 00:30:36,798
I swear to god
l'd break his neck.

720
00:30:39,103 --> 00:30:40,593
No big brother?

721
00:30:43,241 --> 00:30:44,606
No.

722
00:30:47,745 --> 00:30:51,146
No one to take care
of me, you know?

723
00:30:55,420 --> 00:30:59,413
Kelly, l'll try to
help you any way I can,

724
00:30:59,490 --> 00:31:02,982
but you have to
file for divorce.

725
00:31:03,061 --> 00:31:05,894
Do it now while you're
in the hospital

726
00:31:05,964 --> 00:31:07,625
being treated
for the last beating.

727
00:31:07,699 --> 00:31:09,132
lt'll sail through.

728
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:11,998
What better proof
is there than that?

729
00:31:12,070 --> 00:31:16,234
I...I can't file
for a divorce.

730
00:31:17,275 --> 00:31:19,300
Why not?

731
00:31:19,377 --> 00:31:21,641
Because he'll kill me.

732
00:31:23,581 --> 00:31:26,516
He tells me so
all the time.

733
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:30,844
That's not gonna happen.

734
00:31:30,922 --> 00:31:33,220
Could you pass me
a pillow, please,

735
00:31:33,291 --> 00:31:36,021
and put it under my foot?

736
00:31:36,094 --> 00:31:37,823
There's one over there.

737
00:31:47,272 --> 00:31:48,432
Here.

738
00:31:51,276 --> 00:31:52,334
That ok?

739
00:31:52,410 --> 00:31:53,377
Yeah.

740
00:31:53,444 --> 00:31:55,139
Yeah? All right.

741
00:31:55,213 --> 00:31:57,204
Could you pass me
my gown, too, please?

742
00:31:57,282 --> 00:31:58,579
Yeah.

743
00:31:59,851 --> 00:32:01,580
Thanks.

744
00:32:01,653 --> 00:32:03,883
You need some help
putting it on?

745
00:32:03,955 --> 00:32:06,150
No. Just turn around.

746
00:32:06,224 --> 00:32:07,953
All right.

747
00:32:20,038 --> 00:32:22,097
[Rustling]

748
00:32:27,445 --> 00:32:28,571
Hey!

749
00:32:28,646 --> 00:32:30,273
Oh! Who are you?

750
00:32:30,348 --> 00:32:31,975
I live here.
Who the hell are you?

751
00:32:32,050 --> 00:32:33,915
Oh, my gosh.
l'm Delbert's wife.

752
00:32:33,985 --> 00:32:35,748
Delbert? Who the hell
is Delbert?

753
00:32:35,820 --> 00:32:37,014
How did you get in here?

754
00:32:37,088 --> 00:32:38,749
Birdie gave me the key.
[Blows Whistle]

755
00:32:38,823 --> 00:32:39,721
Who are you?

756
00:32:39,791 --> 00:32:41,088
I am the person
who lives here.

757
00:32:41,159 --> 00:32:42,091
Do you understand that?

758
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:43,184
You have no right
to be in here.

759
00:32:43,261 --> 00:32:44,421
This is
a private residence.

760
00:32:44,495 --> 00:32:46,190
Oh, yeah, right.
Some place. Get a grip.

761
00:32:46,264 --> 00:32:49,097
Birdie wants to see you.

762
00:32:49,167 --> 00:32:51,635
[Man Murmuring]

763
00:32:51,703 --> 00:32:53,193
"Agreements are permanent,

764
00:32:53,271 --> 00:32:56,729
and restrictions
mentioned above herein..."

765
00:32:56,808 --> 00:32:58,400
What is this?

766
00:32:58,476 --> 00:33:00,410
Well, you must
be the lawyer.

767
00:33:00,478 --> 00:33:01,445
l'm Rudy Baylor.

768
00:33:01,512 --> 00:33:04,037
l'm Delbert Birdsong,
Birdie's youngest.

769
00:33:04,115 --> 00:33:05,343
He yelled at me.

770
00:33:05,416 --> 00:33:07,611
He told me to get out
of his apartment.

771
00:33:07,685 --> 00:33:08,583
That so?

772
00:33:08,653 --> 00:33:09,847
You're damn right
that's so.

773
00:33:09,921 --> 00:33:10,888
That goes
for the both of you.

774
00:33:10,955 --> 00:33:12,388
I don't want neither one
of you up there

775
00:33:12,457 --> 00:33:13,424
going through my stuff.

776
00:33:13,491 --> 00:33:14,423
That's private property.

777
00:33:14,492 --> 00:33:15,754
