01:23:38,759 --> 01:23:41,319
Not like that,
to me.

1831
01:23:42,830 --> 01:23:43,990
Drummond: Approach
the witness, Your Honor?

1832
01:23:44,064 --> 01:23:45,463
Kipler: You may.

1833
01:23:45,533 --> 01:23:51,233
Mrs. Black, is this not
Dr. Page's letterhead?

1834
01:23:51,305 --> 01:23:54,297
And at the bottom there,
is that not his signature?

1835
01:23:54,375 --> 01:23:56,138
[Whispering]
He can't do that.

1836
01:23:56,210 --> 01:23:57,609
Why?

1837
01:23:57,678 --> 01:23:58,667
Because he can't
introduce evidence

1838
01:23:58,746 --> 01:24:00,976
that way.
Plus it's hearsay.

1839
01:24:01,048 --> 01:24:02,879
Objection, Your Honor.

1840
01:24:02,950 --> 01:24:06,852
A--A letter from--from
the Blacks' family physician

1841
01:24:06,921 --> 01:24:08,980
to Mr. Drummond
is inadmissible.

1842
01:24:09,056 --> 01:24:10,956
Drummond: That is quite
correct, Your Honor.

1843
01:24:11,025 --> 01:24:12,856
And l'm not asking
for this letter

1844
01:24:12,927 --> 01:24:14,326
to be admitted
into evidence.

1845
01:24:14,395 --> 01:24:17,023
l'm simply asking
that this witness

1846
01:24:17,097 --> 01:24:18,155
be allowed
to read the letter

1847
01:24:18,232 --> 01:24:19,961
under rule 612
of the Tennessee

1848
01:24:20,034 --> 01:24:21,296
rules of evidence.

1849
01:24:21,368 --> 01:24:23,165
So her recollection
can be refreshed.

1850
01:24:23,237 --> 01:24:25,671
Kipler: Mr. Baylor,
what do you say?

1851
01:24:25,739 --> 01:24:27,297
I don't know, Your Honor.

1852
01:24:27,374 --> 01:24:28,500
I just object to this.

1853
01:24:28,576 --> 01:24:32,342
And also we were not
furnished this letter

1854
01:24:32,413 --> 01:24:33,812
in pre-trial discovery.

1855
01:24:33,881 --> 01:24:36,349
What do you say
to that, Mr. Drummond?

1856
01:24:36,417 --> 01:24:38,146
I had no idea this
letter would be needed.

1857
01:24:38,219 --> 01:24:39,914
I expected this lady
to tell the truth

1858
01:24:39,987 --> 01:24:41,420
about what her doctor
told her.

1859
01:24:43,624 --> 01:24:45,717
Anything else, Mr. Baylor?

1860
01:24:47,862 --> 01:24:49,329
No.

1861
01:24:51,465 --> 01:24:52,625
Kipler: Mr. Drummond,

1862
01:24:52,700 --> 01:24:55,362
l'm gonna give you
a little latitude,

1863
01:24:55,436 --> 01:24:57,063
but don't stray too far.

1864
01:24:57,137 --> 01:24:59,697
Very well, Your Honor.
Now, Mrs. Black,

1865
01:24:59,773 --> 01:25:02,333
does that letter refresh
your recollection

1866
01:25:02,409 --> 01:25:04,639
as to whether or not
Donny Ray's leukemia

1867
01:25:04,712 --> 01:25:06,009
was the kind
that could be helped

1868
01:25:06,080 --> 01:25:07,240
with a bone marrow
transplant?

1869
01:25:07,314 --> 01:25:09,612
Well, see, now,
he is not a specialist.

1870
01:25:09,683 --> 01:25:10,615
But he is a licensed,

1871
01:25:10,684 --> 01:25:13,949
experienced,
capable physician

1872
01:25:14,021 --> 01:25:16,751
who lovingly told you
time and time again

1873
01:25:16,824 --> 01:25:20,021
what you quite understandably
did not want to accept:

1874
01:25:20,094 --> 01:25:22,927
That your son
was going to die of leukemia

1875
01:25:22,997 --> 01:25:25,795
despite the best efforts
of medical science.

1876
01:25:25,866 --> 01:25:27,231
ls that not true?

1877
01:25:27,301 --> 01:25:29,861
Mrs. Black: But he wasn't
a specialist.

1878
01:25:29,937 --> 01:25:31,336
I didn't believe him.

1879
01:25:31,405 --> 01:25:34,238
Drummond: Not only did you
not believe him, ma'am,

1880
01:25:34,308 --> 01:25:36,173
but you were less than
truthful with me

1881
01:25:36,243 --> 01:25:37,904
and with this jury
moments ago

1882
01:25:37,978 --> 01:25:39,809
when you told us under oath

1883
01:25:39,880 --> 01:25:42,644
that Dr. Page never said
that your son

1884
01:25:42,716 --> 01:25:45,150
had the type of leukemia
that could not be treated

1885
01:25:45,219 --> 01:25:46,618
by a bone marrow transplant.

1886
01:25:46,687 --> 01:25:48,746
I believe
your exact words were,

1887
01:25:48,822 --> 01:25:50,983
"He never said that.

1888
01:25:51,058 --> 01:25:52,184
Not like that

1889
01:25:52,259 --> 01:25:54,022
to me."

1890
01:25:54,094 --> 01:25:56,995
He wasn't a specialist.

1891
01:25:57,064 --> 01:25:59,362
I just wanted Donny Ray

1892
01:25:59,433 --> 01:26:04,598
to have the best medical
treatment available.

1893
01:26:04,672 --> 01:26:07,197
You'd do the same thing.

1894
01:26:07,274 --> 01:26:09,333
Drummond:
Of course, ma'am.

1895
01:26:09,410 --> 01:26:12,106
Of course.

1896
01:26:12,179 --> 01:26:13,737
That'll be all.

1897
01:26:16,116 --> 01:26:18,311
You may step down,
Mrs. Black.

1898
01:26:25,926 --> 01:26:28,360
I didn't do very good,
did I?

1899
01:26:28,429 --> 01:26:30,021
Oh, no, no,
you did fine.

1900
01:26:30,097 --> 01:26:31,189
You did fine.

1901
01:26:31,265 --> 01:26:33,324
lt's all right.
The jury can see

1902
01:26:33,400 --> 01:26:34,958
exactly what
he's up to.

1903
01:26:35,035 --> 01:26:36,434
The jury can see
what he's up to.

1904
01:26:36,503 --> 01:26:37,470
I need a smoke.

1905
01:26:37,538 --> 01:26:38,436
I know you do.

1906
01:26:38,505 --> 01:26:39,335
We're gonna get
to that later.

1907
01:26:39,406 --> 01:26:40,930
[Thunder]

1908
01:26:41,976 --> 01:26:42,965
[Kelly Sighs]

1909
01:26:43,043 --> 01:26:45,978
I hope he hasn't
changed the locks.

1910
01:26:46,046 --> 01:26:47,604
Are you scared?

1911
01:26:47,681 --> 01:26:49,615
Yeah.

1912
01:26:51,819 --> 01:26:53,514
Let's do it.

1913
01:26:56,757 --> 01:26:58,054
[Thunder]

1914
01:27:20,347 --> 01:27:22,076
What a pig.

1915
01:27:23,017 --> 01:27:24,211
l'm sorry.

1916
01:27:24,284 --> 01:27:26,946
Hurry, Kelly.
Come on.

1917
01:27:29,690 --> 01:27:32,090
There's more of my stuff
in the closet.

1918
01:27:40,601 --> 01:27:43,035
You can't take
everything, Kelly.

1919
01:27:47,074 --> 01:27:48,564
[Lock Turns]

1920
01:27:58,485 --> 01:28:00,544
Kelly: Oh, no.

1921
01:28:01,488 --> 01:28:03,979
Cliff: Hey, hello!

1922
01:28:04,058 --> 01:28:05,582
l'm home!

1923
01:28:06,493 --> 01:28:08,393
Well, what do you know?

1924
01:28:08,462 --> 01:28:11,022
What do we have here?

1925
01:28:11,098 --> 01:28:12,793
What you two been doing
in here, huh?

1926
01:28:12,866 --> 01:28:14,561
Hey, take it easy,
all right?

1927
01:28:14,635 --> 01:28:15,567
Come on, tell me.

1928
01:28:15,636 --> 01:28:16,625
l'm your husband.
Remember that, huh?

1929
01:28:16,703 --> 01:28:17,635
Take it easy, buddy.

1930
01:28:17,704 --> 01:28:18,602
You shut up!

1931
01:28:18,672 --> 01:28:20,367
Hey, listen, buddy,
all right.

1932
01:28:20,441 --> 01:28:21,373
I ain't listening
to nothing!

1933
01:28:21,442 --> 01:28:23,239
Take it easy.

1934
01:28:23,310 --> 01:28:24,242
Aah!

1935
01:28:24,311 --> 01:28:25,209
You hurt me, baby.

1936
01:28:25,279 --> 01:28:26,439
You hurt me so bad.

1937
01:28:26,513 --> 01:28:27,502
[Window Breaks]

1938
01:28:27,581 --> 01:28:29,947
Why are you
doing this to me?!

1939
01:28:30,017 --> 01:28:31,075
No, Cliff!

1940
01:28:35,489 --> 01:28:37,218
Kelly: Run!

1941
01:29:10,023 --> 01:29:11,684
Rudy, Rudy!

1942
01:29:11,758 --> 01:29:12,747
Cliff!

1943
01:29:12,826 --> 01:29:13,884
You idiot,
what are you doing?!

1944
01:29:13,961 --> 01:29:14,928
You see what you did?

1945
01:29:14,995 --> 01:29:16,519
Kelly!

1946
01:29:16,597 --> 01:29:18,531
ls this what you wanted?

1947
01:29:18,599 --> 01:29:19,725
lt's not my fault!

1948
01:29:19,800 --> 01:29:21,768
I love you!
I love you!

1949
01:29:34,515 --> 01:29:36,073
Kelly: Rudy!

1950
01:29:38,485 --> 01:29:41,682
[Rudy Hits Cliff]

1951
01:29:41,755 --> 01:29:43,313
Kelly: Stop it, Rudy.

1952
01:29:43,390 --> 01:29:44,880
Stop.

1953
01:29:44,958 --> 01:29:46,585
Cliff: Ohh.

1954
01:29:46,660 --> 01:29:48,753
Give me the bat
and leave.

1955
01:29:48,829 --> 01:29:50,558
What?

1956
01:29:52,399 --> 01:29:54,731
Give me the bat and leave.

1957
01:29:54,801 --> 01:29:57,395
You were not here tonight.

1958
01:29:57,471 --> 01:29:59,200
Give me the bat.

1959
01:30:13,754 --> 01:30:14,721
Go, Rudy.

1960
01:30:14,788 --> 01:30:16,756
You were not here tonight.

1961
01:30:21,395 --> 01:30:23,386
[Bat Hits Cliff]

1962
01:30:39,913 --> 01:30:41,346
[Starts Engine]

1963
01:30:53,860 --> 01:30:55,760
He's finally killed her.

1964
01:30:55,829 --> 01:30:57,763
No, it's him.
He's dead.

1965
01:30:57,831 --> 01:30:58,855
You sure?

1966
01:30:58,932 --> 01:30:59,899
Just saw her.

1967
01:30:59,967 --> 01:31:01,127
How'd it happen?

1968
01:31:01,201 --> 01:31:02,190
I don't know.

1969
01:31:02,269 --> 01:31:03,964
Rudy: They say
when you commit a murder,

1970
01:31:04,037 --> 01:31:05,334
you make
at least 25 mistakes,

1971
01:31:05,405 --> 01:31:08,533
and later you're lucky
if you remember 5 of 'em.

1972
01:31:08,609 --> 01:31:09,667
lt was self-defense,

1973
01:31:09,743 --> 01:31:11,768
but I can't get past
the fact that he's dead.

1974
01:31:11,845 --> 01:31:14,279
And the mistakes are piling
up in my mind so fast

1975
01:31:14,348 --> 01:31:16,009
I can't think.

1976
01:31:17,818 --> 01:31:19,012
Rudy: But Kelly knew.

1977
01:31:19,086 --> 01:31:20,644
She knew what to do.

1978
01:31:20,721 --> 01:31:22,245
She knew it was time.

1979
01:31:22,322 --> 01:31:25,120
With everything
that was happening

1980
01:31:25,192 --> 01:31:26,955
and all that was at stake,

1981
01:31:27,027 --> 01:31:30,758
her first thought
was for my safety.

1982
01:31:30,831 --> 01:31:33,664
And I left her in there
all alone.

1983
01:31:35,168 --> 01:31:36,965
Damn it!

1984
01:31:37,037 --> 01:31:38,231
God damn you, Kelly!

1985
01:31:38,305 --> 01:31:39,966
What the hell's
going on here?

1986
01:31:40,040 --> 01:31:41,974
What the hell
did you do?

1987
01:31:49,449 --> 01:31:51,076
Man: You killed
my son!

1988
01:31:51,151 --> 01:31:52,243
God damn you!

1989
01:31:59,293 --> 01:32:01,124
[Siren]

1990
01:32:27,220 --> 01:32:29,620
Excuse me.
l'm her lawyer.

1991
01:32:29,690 --> 01:32:32,716
I insist on being here
while she's being questioned.

1992
01:32:32,793 --> 01:32:34,192
This is
your attorney?

1993
01:32:34,261 --> 01:32:35,819
Kelly: Yes, sir.

1994
01:32:37,731 --> 01:32:40,666
I want her released
to my custody.

1995
01:32:40,734 --> 01:32:41,894
I can't do that.

1996
01:32:41,968 --> 01:32:43,868
I don't know what kind
of lawyer you are,

1997
01:32:43,937 --> 01:32:45,427
but we got
a dead body here,

1998
01:32:45,505 --> 01:32:48,372
and bond needs to be set
by a judge.

1999
01:32:48,442 --> 01:32:49,966
l'm going to jail?

2000
01:32:50,043 --> 01:32:52,568
Well, can we arrange
for a private cell?

2001
01:32:52,646 --> 01:32:54,876
Look, asshole,
I don't run the jail.

2002
01:32:54,948 --> 01:32:56,916
You got a better way
of doing things,

2003
01:32:56,983 --> 01:32:59,110
then you need to talk
to the jailer.

2004
01:32:59,186 --> 01:33:01,416
They love lawyers
down there, right?

2005
01:33:01,488 --> 01:33:03,922
Look...

2006
01:33:03,990 --> 01:33:05,924
if your lawyer here
is worth his salt,

2007
01:33:05,992 --> 01:33:07,152
you'll be out of here

2008
01:33:07,227 --> 01:33:09,422
sometime tomorrow if
you can post bond, ok?

2009
01:33:11,531 --> 01:33:13,465
Ok.

2010
01:33:17,804 --> 01:33:18,998
Cop: You got 5.

2011
01:33:19,072 --> 01:33:20,266
Rudy: Thank you.

2012
01:33:26,546 --> 01:33:28,537
They're watching us
through that window there,

2013
01:33:28,615 --> 01:33:31,311
and this room
is probably bugged,

2014
01:33:31,385 --> 01:33:34,411
so just be careful
what you say.

2015
01:33:34,488 --> 01:33:36,319
What does
"manslaughter" mean?

2016
01:33:36,390 --> 01:33:39,257
lt's just murder without
the element of intent.

2017
01:33:39,326 --> 01:33:41,191
How much time
could I get?

2018
01:33:41,261 --> 01:33:42,785
No, no, no, you have
to be convicted first.

2019
01:33:42,863 --> 01:33:45,388
l'm not gonna
let that happen.

2020
01:33:45,465 --> 01:33:48,229
That's not gonna happen.

2021
01:33:51,772 --> 01:33:55,333
Cross your wrists
behind you please, ma'am.

2022
01:34:00,213 --> 01:34:02,181
This way, ma'am.

2023
01:34:05,352 --> 01:34:06,717
[Feedback]

2024
01:34:09,122 --> 01:34:10,646
Mr. Lufkin,

2025
01:34:10,724 --> 01:34:12,589
you are the vice
president of claims

2026
01:34:12,659 --> 01:34:13,990
at Great Benefit,
are you not?

2027
01:34:14,060 --> 01:34:15,084
Lufkin: Yes, I am.

2028
01:34:15,162 --> 01:34:15,992
Approach the witness,
Your Honor?

2029
01:34:16,062 --> 01:34:17,359
You may.

2030
01:34:19,599 --> 01:34:21,999
You recognize this?

2031
01:34:22,068 --> 01:34:23,126
Go on.

2032
01:34:25,305 --> 01:34:27,398
Rudy: Read that
to the jury.

2033
01:34:30,177 --> 01:34:31,269
"Dear Mrs. Black,

2034
01:34:31,344 --> 01:34:32,675
On 7 prior occasions

2035
01:34:32,746 --> 01:34:34,611
this company has denied
your claim in writing.

2036
01:34:34,681 --> 01:34:36,308
We now deny it
for the eighth and final time.

2037
01:34:36,383 --> 01:34:38,442
You must be stupid,
stupid, stupid.

2038
01:34:38,518 --> 01:34:40,179
Sincerely Everett Lufkin,

2039
01:34:40,253 --> 01:34:42,084
Vice President, Claims."

2040
01:34:42,155 --> 01:34:44,146
That's you?

2041
01:34:44,224 --> 01:34:45,418
Yes.

2042
01:34:47,861 --> 01:34:49,488
How do you explain that?

2043
01:34:54,935 --> 01:34:57,563
lt was a difficult time
for me personally.

2044
01:34:57,637 --> 01:35:00,162
I was under
a lot of stress.

2045
01:35:00,240 --> 01:35:03,732
We had denied this claim
7 times before.

2046
01:35:03,810 --> 01:35:06,404
I was trying to be emphatic.

2047
01:35:06,480 --> 01:35:08,072
I snapped.

2048
01:35:08,148 --> 01:35:09,672
I regret
having written the letter,

2049
01:35:09,749 --> 01:35:12,183
and I apologize.

2050
01:35:12,252 --> 01:35:13,480
Don't you think
it's a little late

2051
01:35:13,553 --> 01:35:14,747
for an apology?

2052
01:35:16,556 --> 01:35:18,285
Maybe.

2053
01:35:18,358 --> 01:35:19,325
Maybe?

2054
01:35:19,392 --> 01:35:21,360
The boy is dead,
isn't he?

2055
01:35:24,798 --> 01:35:27,392
Yes.

2056
01:35:27,467 --> 01:35:29,401
Now, Mr. Lufkin,

2057
01:35:29,469 --> 01:35:31,767
who is Jackie Lemancyzk?

2058
01:35:31,838 --> 01:35:37,743
Jackie Lemancyzk
is a former claims handler.

2059
01:35:37,811 --> 01:35:39,642
And did she work
in your department?

2060
01:35:39,713 --> 01:35:40,645
Yes.

2061
01:35:40,714 --> 01:35:42,807
And when did she
stop working

2062
01:35:42,883 --> 01:35:43,850
for Great Benefit?

2063
01:35:43,917 --> 01:35:46,681
I don't remember the day.

2064
01:35:46,753 --> 01:35:48,687
How about October 30?

2065
01:35:48,755 --> 01:35:50,188
Sounds close.

2066
01:35:50,257 --> 01:35:52,521
Wasn't that just 2 days
before she was scheduled

2067
01:35:52,592 --> 01:35:54,457
to give a deposition
in this case?

2068
01:35:54,528 --> 01:35:56,086
I really don't remember.

2069
01:35:56,162 --> 01:35:58,858
l'd like to refresh the
witness' recollection

2070
01:35:58,932 --> 01:36:01,594
under rule 612.

2071
01:36:04,271 --> 01:36:05,636
October 30th.

2072
01:36:05,705 --> 01:36:06,831
Apparently.

2073
01:36:06,907 --> 01:36:08,067
And that was just 2 days
before she was scheduled

2074
01:36:08,141 --> 01:36:09,165
to give a deposition
in this matter?

2075
01:36:09,242 --> 01:36:10,869
I guess so.

2076
01:36:10,944 --> 01:36:12,343
And she was
the person responsible

2077
01:36:12,412 --> 01:36:13,902
for handling
Donny Ray Black's claim,

2078
01:36:13,980 --> 01:36:14,878
was she not?

2079
01:36:14,948 --> 01:36:16,745
That's correct.

2080
01:36:16,816 --> 01:36:18,113
And you fired her?

2081
01:36:20,153 --> 01:36:22,280
Of course not.

2082
01:36:22,355 --> 01:36:24,687
Well, how'd you
get rid of her?

2083
01:36:24,758 --> 01:36:25,850
She resigned.

2084
01:36:25,926 --> 01:36:28,394
lt's right here in the letter
you just gave me.

2085
01:36:28,461 --> 01:36:29,985
Oh. Why'd she resign?

2086
01:36:31,565 --> 01:36:34,227
"I hereby resign
for personal reasons"

2087
01:36:34,301 --> 01:36:35,734
So it was her idea

2088
01:36:35,802 --> 01:36:37,429
to leave her job?

2089
01:36:37,504 --> 01:36:38,596
That's what it says.

2090
01:36:38,672 --> 01:36:40,731
Nothing further.

2091
01:36:40,807 --> 01:36:42,798
Judge Kipler:
You may step down, sir.

2092
01:36:43,743 --> 01:36:44,801
[Feedback]

2093
01:36:49,683 --> 01:36:51,082
Man: Hello.

2094
01:36:51,151 --> 01:36:55,986
Hi. l'm Jackie Lemancyzk's
brother James.

2095
